      </svg>
      <!-- Star 2 (filled) -->
      <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-amber-400" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
        <path d="M9.049 2.927c.3-.921 1.603-.921 1.902 0l1.07 3.292a1 1 0 00.95.69h3.462c.969 0 1.371 1.24.588 1.81l-2.8 2.034a1 1 0 00-.364 1.118l1.07 3.292c.3.921-.755 1.688-1.54 1.118l-2.8-2.034a1 1 0 00-1.175 0l-2.8 2.034c-.784.57-1.838-.197-1.539-1.118l1.07-3.292a1 1 0 00-.364-1.118L2.98 8.72c-.783-.57-.38-1.81.588-1.81h3.461a1 1 0 00.951-.69l1.07-3.292z" />
      </svg>
      <!-- Star 3 (filled) -->
      <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-amber-400" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
        <path d="M9.049 2.927c.3-.921 1.603-.921 1.902 0l1.07 3.292a1 1 0 00.95.69h3.462c.969 0 1.371 1.24.588 1.81l-2.8 2.034a1 1 0 00-.364 1.118l1.07 3.292c.3.921-.755 1.688-1.54 1.118l-2.8-2.034a1 1 0 00-1.175 0l-2.8 2.034c-.784.57-1.838-.197-1.539-1.118l1.07-3.292a1 1 0 00-.364-1.118L2.98 8.72c-.783-.57-.38-1.81.588-1.81h3.461a1 1 0 00.951-.69l1.07-3.292z" />
      </svg>
      <!-- Star 4 (filled) -->
      <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-amber-400" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
        <path d="M9.049 2.927c.3-.921 1.603-.921 1.902 0l1.07 3.292a1 1 0 00.95.69h3.462c.969 0 1.371 1.24.588 1.81l-2.8 2.034a1 1 0 00-.364 1.118l1.07 3.292c.3.921-.755 1.688-1.54 1.118l-2.8-2.034a1 1 0 00-1.175 0l-2.8 2.034c-.784.57-1.838-.197-1.539-1.118l1.07-3.292a1 1 0 00-.364-1.118L2.98 8.72c-.783-.57-.38-1.81.588-1.81h3.461a1 1 0 00.951-.69l1.07-3.292z" />
      </svg>
      <!-- Star 5 (partial - ~80% filled for 3.8 rating) -->
      <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-slate-300" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
        <defs>
          <linearGradient id="partial-star-tovuti">
            <stop offset="80%" stop-color="#fbbf24" />
            <stop offset="80%" stop-color="#cbd5e1" />
          </linearGradient>
        </defs>
        <path fill="url(#partial-star-tovuti)" d="M9.049 2.927c.3-.921 1.603-.921 1.902 0l1.07 3.292a1 1 0 00.95.69h3.462c.969 0 1.371 1.24.588 1.81l-2.8 2.034a1 1 0 00-.364 1.118l1.07 3.292c.3.921-.755 1.688-1.54 1.118l-2.8-2.034a1 1 0 00-1.175 0l-2.8 2.034c-.784.57-1.838-.197-1.539-1.118l1.07-3.292a1 1 0 00-.364-1.118L2.98 8.72c-.783-.57-.38-1.81.588-1.81h3.461a1 1 0 00.951-.69l1.07-3.292z" />
      </svg>
    </div>
    <span class="text-lg font-semibold text-navy">3.8 / 5</span>
  </div>

  <!-- Summary Verdict -->
  <div class="bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
    <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
      <strong>The bottom line:</strong> Tovuti stands out for organizations that need to create engaging, interactive training content without purchasing separate authoring tools. With 40+ built-in content types including interactive video and branching scenarios, it eliminates the need for expensive eLearning software. The trade-offs are a less polished learner experience compared to consumer-focused platforms and a steeper learning curve for administrators. If built-in authoring is your priority, Tovuti delivers genuine value.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Who this is for -->
  <p class="text-slate-600 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
    This review is written for L&D managers, training directors, and HR professionals evaluating LMS platforms with content creation capabilities. If your organization needs to build custom training materials without investing in separate authoring tools, this review will help you determine if Tovuti fits your requirements.
  </p>

  <!-- Key Takeaways -->
  <KeyTakeaways items={[
    "Tovuti includes built-in course authoring with 40+ interactive content types—no separate software required.",
    "Interactive video capabilities include clickable hotspots, branching, quizzes embedded in video, and time-stamped annotations.",
    "White-label options allow complete branding customization including custom domains, colors, logos, and CSS.",
    "Pricing is quote-based and scales with active users, not total registered users.",
    "The platform supports both internal employee training and external customer education with eCommerce features.",
    "User interface is functional but less polished than consumer-focused learning platforms."
  ]} />

  <!-- What is Tovuti? -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4">What is Tovuti LMS?</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Tovuti is a cloud-based Learning Management System designed for organizations that need to create, manage, and deliver training programs. Founded in 2018 and based in Nevada, the platform has positioned itself around a key differentiator: comprehensive built-in course authoring that eliminates the need for separate content creation tools.
    </p>
    <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Most enterprise LMS platforms require organizations to purchase and integrate separate authoring tools like Articulate Storyline or Adobe Captivate. Tovuti takes a different approach, providing a comprehensive authoring suite directly within the platform. This includes over 40 interactive content types, a visual course builder, assessment tools, and interactive video capabilities.
    </p>
    <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
      Tovuti serves both internal training use cases (employee onboarding, compliance, skills development) and external training (customer education, partner training, paid courses). The platform includes white-labeling, eCommerce, and subscription billing for external training programs. It's SCORM-compliant and supports content imports from external authoring tools when needed.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Who is Tovuti Best For? -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4">Who is Tovuti Best For?</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
      Tovuti fits specific organizational needs better than others. Here's where it works best:
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-4">
      <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-5">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy mb-2">Organizations Without Authoring Tools</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          If your organization hasn't invested in eLearning authoring software and wants to avoid that expense, Tovuti's built-in tools provide immediate content creation capabilities. The 40+ content types cover most training scenarios without additional software purchases.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-5">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy mb-2">Interactive Content Needs</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Organizations that need more than basic video and PDF courses benefit from Tovuti's interactive capabilities. Branching scenarios, gamified elements, and interactive video create more engaging learning experiences than passive content consumption.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-5">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy mb-2">Mid-Market Companies</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Tovuti's pricing and feature set aligns well with mid-market organizations—too sophisticated for small business tools but not as complex or expensive as enterprise platforms like Docebo or Cornerstone. Companies with 100-5,000 employees often find the sweet spot.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-5">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy mb-2">Training Departments with Diverse Content</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          L&D teams that create varied content types—compliance training, product education, soft skills, onboarding—benefit from the flexibility of 40+ content types. One platform handles multiple training use cases without tool switching.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Core Capabilities -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4">Core Capabilities</h2>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-navy mt-6 mb-3">Built-In Course Authoring</h3>
    <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Tovuti's authoring suite includes a drag-and-drop course builder with 40+ content types: interactive video, branching scenarios, drag-and-drop activities, memory games, flashcards, image hotspots, timelines, checklists, accordions, tabs, flip cards, and more. Courses can include assessments with 10+ question types including multiple choice, true/false, fill-in-the-blank, matching, sequencing, and essay questions.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-navy mt-6 mb-3">Interactive Video</h3>
    <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      The interactive video feature allows you to add clickable hotspots, branching decision points, embedded quizzes, and time-stamped annotations to video content. Viewers can click on elements within the video to learn more, answer questions to proceed, or branch to different content based on their choices. This transforms passive video watching into active learning experiences.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-navy mt-6 mb-3">Learning Management</h3>
    <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Core LMS features include user management, course assignments, learning paths, prerequisites, drip scheduling, and automated reminders. The platform supports blended learning with instructor-led sessions, webinars, and self-paced content. Compliance tracking includes certification management, expiration notifications, and audit-ready reporting.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-navy mt-6 mb-3">Assessments and Certifications</h3>
    <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Assessment capabilities include customizable quizzes, surveys, and exams with multiple question types. Features include question randomization, time limits, attempt limits, and question banks. Certificates are auto-generated upon completion and can be customized with your branding. Skills tracking and competency mapping help identify knowledge gaps.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-navy mt-6 mb-3">White-Label and Branding</h3>
    <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Tovuti offers extensive white-labeling options including custom domains, logo and color customization, custom CSS for advanced styling, and branded email notifications. The learner portal can be fully customized to match your organization's look and feel, creating a seamless brand experience.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-navy mt-6 mb-3">eCommerce and Monetization</h3>
    <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      For external training programs, Tovuti includes eCommerce with Stripe and PayPal integration. Sell individual courses, subscriptions, or bundled offerings. Features include coupon codes, discount rules, affiliate tracking, and detailed sales reporting. The platform supports both B2C and B2B sales models.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-navy mt-6 mb-3">Integrations</h3>
    <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Tovuti integrates with common business tools including Salesforce, HubSpot, Zoom, Microsoft Teams, Slack, and various HRIS systems. The platform offers SSO via SAML 2.0, API access for custom integrations, and webhooks for automated workflows. Content can be imported via SCORM, xAPI, and AICC standards.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Key Strengths -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4">Key Strengths</h2>

    <div class="space-y-5">
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy mb-1">Comprehensive Built-In Authoring</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
          The 40+ content types and visual course builder eliminate the need for separate authoring software. This reduces costs, simplifies workflows, and ensures content is natively integrated with the LMS. Organizations save thousands in software licenses and training time.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy mb-1">Interactive Video Capabilities</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
          Few LMS platforms offer truly interactive video at this price point. The ability to add hotspots, branching, and embedded quizzes transforms standard training videos into engaging learning experiences without specialized video editing tools.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy mb-1">Active User Pricing Model</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
          Tovuti charges based on active users (those who actually engage with training) rather than total registered users. For organizations with large employee bases but intermittent training needs, this pricing model can be significantly more cost-effective than alternatives.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy mb-1">Flexible Content Options</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
          The platform supports both native content creation and standard imports (SCORM, xAPI, AICC). This flexibility means you're not locked in—content created in Tovuti can be exported, and existing content libraries can be imported without recreation.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy mb-1">Strong White-Labeling</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
          The white-label capabilities go beyond basic logo replacement to include custom CSS, branded emails, and fully customized learner portals. Organizations can create training experiences that feel completely native to their brand.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy mb-1">All-in-One Value</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
          By combining LMS, authoring, eCommerce, and assessment in one platform, Tovuti reduces tool sprawl. One system to learn, one vendor relationship, one integrated experience for both administrators and learners.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Where Tovuti May Not Be the Best Fit -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4">Where Tovuti May Not Be the Best Fit</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Honest evaluation requires acknowledging limitations. Here is where Tovuti falls short:
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-5">
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy mb-1">Learner Experience Polish</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
          The learner interface is functional but lacks the polish of consumer-focused platforms like Thinkific or Teachable. Navigation can feel cluttered, and the mobile experience, while usable, doesn't match the refinement of dedicated learning commerce platforms.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy mb-1">Steep Admin Learning Curve</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
          The comprehensive feature set comes with complexity. New administrators often report a learning curve in understanding the platform's structure and capabilities. Training and documentation are necessary to leverage the full feature set effectively.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy mb-1">Limited Advanced LMS Features</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
          Compared to enterprise platforms like Docebo or Cornerstone, Tovuti lacks some advanced features like AI-powered recommendations, sophisticated skills management, deep analytics, and extensive automation workflows. It's a capable LMS but not an enterprise learning suite.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy mb-1">Quote-Based Pricing Transparency</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
          Without published pricing, budgeting can be challenging. The sales process requires consultation, and pricing varies based on negotiation. Organizations wanting pricing transparency may find this frustrating.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy mb-1">Smaller Ecosystem</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
          Tovuti has a smaller user community and fewer third-party integrations than larger platforms. Finding freelancers, templates, or community support resources can be more difficult than with established competitors.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing Overview -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4">Pricing Overview</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Tovuti uses quote-based pricing that scales with your active user count. Pricing typically starts in the $700-$1,000 per month range for smaller implementations and increases based on user volume and feature requirements.
    </p>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-slate-200 mb-4">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-navy text-white">
            <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 font-semibold">Pricing Factor</th>
            <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 font-semibold">Details</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="bg-white border-t border-slate-200">
            <td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium text-navy">User Model</td>
            <td class="py-3 px-4 text-slate-600">Active users (those who log in and engage), not total registered users</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-slate-50 border-t border-slate-200">
            <td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium text-navy">Starting Price</td>
            <td class="py-3 px-4 text-slate-600">Approximately $700-$1,000/month for smaller implementations</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-white border-t border-slate-200">
            <td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium text-navy">Contract Terms</td>
            <td class="py-3 px-4 text-slate-600">Annual contracts typical; monthly options may be available</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-slate-50 border-t border-slate-200">
            <td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium text-navy">Implementation</td>
            <td class="py-3 px-4 text-slate-600">Setup and training typically included or available as add-on</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      <strong>What's Included:</strong> All plans include the full authoring suite, LMS features, assessments, basic integrations, and white-labeling. eCommerce and advanced integrations may be tier-dependent.
    </p>

    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">
      Pricing is quote-based. Contact Tovuti directly for current pricing specific to your user count and requirements.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- How Tovuti Compares -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4">How Tovuti Compares</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Here's how Tovuti stacks up against other platforms with content creation capabilities:
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable
      headers={["Tovuti", "Thinkific", "Articulate + LMS", "LearnDash", "Absorb"]}
      highlight={0}
      rows={[
        { feature: "Primary Focus", values: ["Built-in authoring LMS", "Learning commerce", "Content creation", "WordPress LMS", "Enterprise training"] },
        { feature: "Built-In Authoring", values: ["Yes—40+ types", "Basic", "N/A (separate tool)", "Via plugins", "Limited"] },
        { feature: "Best For", values: ["Interactive content needs", "Selling courses", "Content specialists", "WordPress users", "Enterprise compliance"] },
        { feature: "Interactive Video", values: ["Yes—native", "Basic", "Via Storyline", "Via plugins", "Limited"] },
        { feature: "Pricing Model", values: ["Quote-based", "Published tiers", "Tool + LMS cost", "Plugin + hosting", "Quote-based"] },
        { feature: "Ease of Setup", values: ["Moderate", "Fast", "Complex", "WordPress dependent", "Implementation"] },
        { feature: "Learner Experience", values: ["Functional", "Polished", "Varies", "WordPress dependent", "Professional"] }
      ]}
    />
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <LeadFormModal
    variant="inline"
    ctaTitle="Evaluating whether this platform fits your needs?"
    ctaDescription="Get a personalized recommendation based on your content needs, team size, and training goals."
    ctaButtonText="Get My Recommendation"
